<h2>
    <strong>Introduction to Summer Steelhead Fishing</strong>
</h2>
<p>
    Summer steelhead fishing in Oregon is not just a pastime—it’s a passion. These acrobatic fish are known for their powerful runs and aerial displays, offering one of the most thrilling angling experiences in the Pacific Northwest. Unlike winter steelhead, summer steelhead begin entering rivers around late spring and are available through early fall. This gives anglers a longer and often more productive window to fish.
</p>
<p>
    Their journey from the ocean to inland tributaries provides ample opportunities for bank and boat anglers alike. With their silvery flash and strong will, summer steelhead are often called “the fish of a thousand casts”—but once hooked, the reward is unforgettable.
</p>
