<h2>
    <strong>Fishing Techniques for Summer Steelhead</strong>
</h2>
<h3>
    <strong>Drift Fishing</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    This classic method involves bouncing bait off the river bottom. Popular baits include roe, nightcrawlers, and sand shrimp. Ensure you use just enough weight to tap the bottom gently.
</p>
<h3>
    <strong>Fly Fishing</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    Fly anglers love the challenge of summer steelhead. Use weighted nymphs or swinging streamers on sink-tip lines. The Sandy River’s clearer water is ideal for fly presentation.
</p>
<h3>
    <strong>Spin Casting</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    Spinners like Blue Fox Vibrax or Mepps Aglia work well in riffles and tailouts. Match your rod and reel to handle long battles and fast currents.
</p>
